# Git Workflow

## Never do without explicit instruction

- **Never push to `main`** — not under any circumstances, unless the owner explicitly says "push to main"
- **Never merge into `main`** without explicit instruction
- **Never push at all** without an explicit command from the owner
- **Never commit** without an explicit request

## Required workflow

1. Make code changes
2. Report what was done — wait for owner to review
3. Only commit after an explicit "commit" instruction
4. Only push after an explicit "push" instruction — always to a **feature branch**, never to `main`
5. Only push to `main` after an explicit "push to main" or "merge to main" instruction

## Branches

- All changes go through a dedicated feature branch (e.g. `feature/auth-refactor`)
- `git push origin main` is **forbidden** without a direct "push to main" instruction
- Name the branch after the task or propose a name to the owner
